- "Ventured into the most unique configurations" refers to the distinct configurations accessed by users;
- "Explored" refers to the act of accessing configurations.

- "frequented by configurations" refers to the number of configurations associated with each template;
- "utilized on average" is calculated by dividing the count of distinct configurations by the total number of configurations for each template;
- "recently accessed" means configurations that have a recorded access date;
- "non-zero total template size" indicates that configurations must have associated document templates with a size greater than zero.

